# Branching Model (authoritative)

See **`docs/ops/git-and-deploy.md`** for the full solo-developer deploy loop.

## Branches

| Branch | Role | Deploys to |
|--------|------|------------|
| **`main`** | Production source of truth | equipqr.app (after Production Release Readiness + `vercel promote`) |
| **`preview`** | Integration / pre-production train | **`preview.equipqr.app`** (Vercel Preview domain bound to this branch) |
| **`feat/*`, `fix/*`, etc.** | Short-lived work branches | Vercel **Preview** â†’ commit-specific `*.vercel.app` URL |

There is **no `dev` branch**. Git **`preview`** is the default merge target for feature work.

## Rules for agents

1. **Branch off `preview`** for new feature, fix, refactor, chore, or experimental work.
2. **Day-to-day PRs target `preview`.** Production ships via a controlled **`preview` â†’ `main`** PR (or `/release` promote path).
3. When GitHub defaults or old docs disagree, **this rule wins** for day-to-day work.
4. Before creating a branch:
   ```powershell
   git fetch origin preview
   git switch -c feat/<short-name> origin/preview
   ```
5. When opening a feature/fix PR:
   ```powershell
   gh pr create --base preview --head feat/<short-name> --title "<conventional-commit title>"
   ```
6. **Changelog / version discipline:**
   - PRs into **`preview`**: accumulate notes under CHANGELOG `[Unreleased]`; **do not** bump `package.json` / lockfile app version.
   - PRs into **`main`** (from `preview` / release): semver bump, versioned CHANGELOG section, empty `[Unreleased]` after cut.
7. **Pre-production testing:**
   - **Primary:** commit-specific Vercel Preview URL after pushing a work branch, and/or **`preview.equipqr.app`** after merge to `preview`.
   - **Supabase:** no perpetual preview database. Cloud `preview.equipqr.app` uses **production** Supabase for ordinary (non-schema) QA. Use a properly seeded **ephemeral** Supabase PR branch only when actively testing `supabase/**` schema/RLS/migrations.
   - OAuth (Google Workspace, QuickBooks): verify on the **local stack** before merge.
8. **Hotfix:** Prefer `fix/*` â†’ `preview` then promote; for production-only emergencies, branch off `origin/main`, PR into `main`, then back-merge/rebase `preview` so the train does not diverge permanently.
9. **Local E2E before push/PR.** No push and no PR open until `local-verify-before-preview-push.mdc` passes with zero user manual steps.
10. **Worktree tempo:**
    - Feature work: merge-ready PR into **`preview`** per `pr-merge-ready-workflow.mdc`.
    - Production: merge-ready **`preview` â†’ `main`** (or `chore/release-v*` from curated preview tip).
    - **Never force-push to `main` or `preview`.**

See git-powershell.mdc for Windows worktree cleanup gotchas.
